docs.text: Welcome to Kangals Documentation Kangal is under active development. Kangal is a Quadruped Robot Dog based on the Work of Baris Alp. Check it out here: https://grabcad.com/library/diy-quadruped-robot-1. This Project aims do document the build Process for Hard- and Software, Calibration and where to get the different needed Hardware Parts. Code, .stl, .step Files and more can be found here https://github.com/lichtwellenreiter/diy-kangal Commands mkdocs new [dir-name] - Create a new project. mkdocs serve - Start the live-reloading docs server. mkdocs build - Build the documentation site. mkdocs -h - Print help message and exit. Project layout mkdocs.yml # The configuration file. docs/ index.md # The documentation homepage. ... # Other markdown pages, images and other files.
